   <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.darkora.net/img/external/dark.jpg width=80 length=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Writing Exercises...anyone interested?</span><hr size=1>   Well, I was thinking of posting weekly topics of exercises for aspiring writers to get some more practice...but I just want to check the interest levels first.  Let me know if you think something like that would be helpful to you as a writer.  I'm planning on trying to keep it fairly generalized since we have a bunch of short story/poetry writers (and oddly enough, not too many comic/manga script writers from what I've seen), but if there's anything you'd like to suggest for something you'd like to work on, let me know.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/24/01 2:10:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing Exercises...anyone interested?</span><hr size=1> I think this would be cool...I don't know If i'd have the time to participate but it'd be cool...<br>
what would it be...taking some vague ideas of a story and saying &quot;ok there you go...now make it live&quot;<br>
if you do that...you can have a bunch of cool elements<br>
the type of main character...not to detailed so there's lots of room to develop...but enough info so there's something to start from because thinking up characters is a lot of trouble<br>
do the same thing with the main villain <br>
and do the settings for the critical points in the story...again leave a lot of room for development...something vague like...&quot;a boat&quot; would be good...<br>
and maybe outline some of the things in the plot you'd like to see or certain scenes...ect...like what the crisis and maybe say you want a massive fight scene between friends before the climax<br>
and add some optional stuff that can lead to some serious customization...<br>
like secondary settings and characters and other things that would lead to sub plots and maybe something like a problem that keeps the main characters from getting to their goal in an easy way...like a saboteur or maybe a main road is blocked...ect<br>
<br>
using less of these would mean more freedom...but it's easier to write quickly when you have all the ideas there...all you have to do is flesh it out...so you'd have to find the balance between freedom and speed...I think optional stuff would help that<br>
<br>
I guess that'd be good for short stories...that's basically what I do for practice when I feel like it...<br>
poetry I have no idea...it's restrictive in itself...and it's short enough that suggesting certain elements wouldn't help much...<br>
scripts is just taking a story and seperating the visual and dialogue...and deciding what view would look good for a certain part of the story <p><pre>
--
%) Picasso Smilie
---               
Single Handedly saving the porn industry
--
I'm a little out of wack...
If you happen to have any extra whack please contact me...
Thank you
--
</pre></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udjaitchtoooh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DJAitchTooOh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/24/01 9:50:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://unsupported.usc.edu/~efn/DJIcon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing Exercises...anyone interested?</span><hr size=1> Yeah,  I feel pretty much the same as Jefm.  It would be really cool to have them, but I'm not sure I'd have time to reply.  (Scratches head) Any variety is certainly welcome by me....<br>
<br>
Suggestions..... hmm...  well,  I guess techniques for character development would be good...  (like throwing darts at a traitboard,  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )  Outlining,  organization and stuff,  above and beyond just creating plots.... (shrugs)  Just a suggestion,  though...<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/24/01 10:16:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing Exercises...anyone interested?</span><hr size=1> Character development is always tricky...that's usually what I do first before I start writing...<br>
it's neccessary for main characters...and any minor ones that will be around for a while...<br>
you have to think of everything to describe them...good...bad...inside and out...EVERYTHING<br>
even if you don't use it you'll want it anyway just incase you decide to add it<br>
making a good character is a bit of art in itself...it takes practice...I'm not sure how to show practice...you could always do up a character when you're bored for use later...<br>
Playing dungeons and dragons is helpful too...if you're a big geek you'll have a big description of your favourite characters<br>
outlining and organization are easy...<br>
the basics...if you don't have any idea how the story will go...take you're ideas and stuff you know you want in it...write it all down...then draw lines connecting them and form units...then number them how you want them to occur in the story<br>
<br>
me I usually have an idea in my head...about how I want it to go...<br>
I'll start with that and keep expanding...<br>
<br>
but I'm not sure how you could practice that...the only way to turn someone on to something like that is to get them to do a story with outlines and character sheets ect and compare it with one done without them...<br>
they'll never go back once they see how much trouble it saves and the level of quality it creates...<br>
if you have any friends into DND see if they'll dig up some character profile sheets for you...those are a great help <p><pre>
--
%) Picasso Smilie
---               
Single Handedly saving the porn industry
--
I'm a little out of wack...
If you happen to have any extra whack please contact me...
Thank you
--
</pre></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udarkora.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Twilight Oracle</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/25/01 11:17:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.darkora.net/img/external/dark.jpg width=80 length=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing Exercises...anyone interested?</span><hr size=1>   D&amp;D geeks write out extensive backgrounds on their characters?  Really?  *looks at stack of folders in the corner each containing 10-20 pages of notes, sketches, history on a single character each*  You're kidding, right?   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Well, the exercises I was planning on putting out were going to be extremely varied and hopefully generic enough so that all the different styles of writers here could participate.  It's funny that character development came up...the first exercise I was planning was to describe a character and their current personality/attitudes/quirks/powers.  Then the goal of the exercise would be to develop a background for the character that caused them to be the way they are now.  How'd they develop those powers?  Why do they act the way they do?  Why are they deathly afraid of cheese?  Well, you get the idea.<br>
<br>
  As for participation, well, I'd put one up every week or two, but that doesn't mean you need to get it done before the next one comes up...add to it when you feel like it or when you just don't have anything going on and want to practice writing.  Also in the thread you'll be able to discuss with people about the different takes everyone had on that activity.  You'll get a glimpse to how other writers think things through and maybe even get ideas for stuff you could work on in your own writings.  It'll be neat!   ^_^ <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udarkora.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOra</A> at: 12/25/01 11:19:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uakumatavlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akuma Tavlore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/25/01 12:21:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing Exercises...anyone interested?</span><hr size=1> Im very Intrested <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/u21kijuuki21.showPublicProfile?language=EN>21Kijuuki21</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/26/01 10:36:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing Exercises...anyone interested?</span><hr size=1> I think that's an excellent idea... I'd be willing to participate in it... been doing it for a couple years now from online RPing with my friends... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udarkora.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Twilight Oracle</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/26/01 11:03:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.darkora.net/img/external/dark.jpg width=80 length=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Writing Exercises...anyone interested?</span><hr size=1> Alrighty...I'll put one up then (and I'll try to add a new exercise on Fridays/weekends).  I'll do the character development one next week...I've got a more &quot;seasonally appropriate&quot; theme for this week's exercise. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showPrevMessage?topicID=432.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showNextMessage?topicID=432.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.emailToFriend?topicID=432.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a hre